# Anti-Card UI Rules
#
# .cursorrules 파일에 이 내용을 그대로 붙여넣으세요.
# 또는 기존 .cursorrules 파일의 한 섹션으로 추가하세요.

You are working on an end-user UI (landing/marketing/content site), NOT an admin dashboard.
Apply the @freeive/anti-card design rules below to all generated UI code.

## NEVER

- DO NOT use shadcn-style Card / CardContent / CardHeader / CardFooter.
- DO NOT wrap every section in `border + rounded + p-6` boxes.
- DO NOT lay out content in 3-column grids of cards.
- DO NOT pursue dense information layout; end-user screens should breathe.

## ALWAYS — five hierarchy patterns

1. SPACE — section padding `py-16 md:py-20` (or larger). 100~160px between sections.
2. CONTRAST — typography size/weight/color hierarchy
   - Hero h1: `text-[clamp(2rem,5vw,4rem)] font-semibold leading-[1.05] tracking-tight`
   - Section h2: `text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight`
3. HAIRLINES — divide regions with 1px lines
   - Section: `border-t border-white/[0.06]`
   - List: `divide-y divide-white/[0.06] border-y border-white/[0.06]`
4. SMALLCAPS LABELS (eyebrow) — categorize regions with a small uppercase label
   - `<p class="text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-zinc-500">Section · Label</p>`
5. LIST ROWS — instead of card grids, use row layouts
   - `<li class="grid grid-cols-[140px_1fr_auto] py-6 gap-8">…</li>`

## Standard patterns

### Hero
```html
<section class="py-24 md:py-32">
  <p class="text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-zinc-500">Eyebrow</p>
  <h1 class="mt-5 max-w-[18ch] text-[clamp(2rem,5vw,4rem)] font-semibold leading-[1.05] tracking-tight">
    Hero heading (3-7 words)
  </h1>
  <p class="mt-7 max-w-[44ch] text-[15.5px] leading-relaxed text-zinc-300">
    Sub copy.
  </p>
</section>
```

### Section
```html
<section class="border-t border-white/[0.06] py-16 md:py-20">
  <p class="text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-zinc-500">Eyebrow</p>
  <h2 class="mt-3 text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Section title.</h2>
  <p class="mt-6 max-w-[58ch] text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-zinc-300">Section description.</p>
  <!-- list or free content -->
</section>
```

### List (instead of card grid)
```html
<ul class="divide-y divide-white/[0.06] border-y border-white/[0.06]">
  <li class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[140px_1fr_auto] gap-3 md:gap-8 py-6">
    <span class="text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-zinc-500">2024</span>
    <span class="text-[15.5px] font-medium">Title</span>
    <span class="text-[12.5px] text-zinc-400">Trailing info</span>
  </li>
</ul>
```

## Color tone (dark default)

- bg: `bg-zinc-950` or `#08090a`
- body: `text-zinc-100` to `text-zinc-300`
- muted: `text-zinc-400` to `text-zinc-500`
- accent: `text-emerald-400` or `#7cf2c4` (one accent only)
- hairlines: `border-white/[0.06]`, `divide-white/[0.06]`

For light mode, invert zinc steps. Hairlines: `border-zinc-200/60`.

## Optional — Layer 2 React components

If using React + Tailwind:
```tsx
import { Eyebrow, SectionFrame, ListRow } from "@freeive/anti-card";

<SectionFrame eyebrow="Heritage · 2016 — Now" title="…">
  <ul className="divide-y divide-white/[0.06] border-y border-white/[0.06]">
    <ListRow meta="2024" trailing="EBS">…</ListRow>
  </ul>
</SectionFrame>
```

But the HTML patterns above must produce the same visual output without these components.

## Self-check before output

All must be YES:
- [ ] No card boxes? (no shadcn Card, no `border rounded p-6` wrapping every section)
- [ ] Headings large enough? (text-2xl or larger)
- [ ] Section padding 80px+ each side?
- [ ] Region divisions use hairlines, not boxes?
- [ ] Smallcaps eyebrow labels used?
- [ ] List layouts use rows, not card grids?

